name: Syllidae, Magelonidae and Maldanidae from the Northwestern Coast of Egypt
description: The data in this dataset results from differentsampling campaigns along the Mediterranean coast of Egypt andthe Suez Channel. Most samples of Polychaetes were taken using a Van Veen grab, while samples from Port SaidHarbour were collected by knife and net used for collectingfauna. Specimens including those of newly describedspecies were deposited at the Marine ReferenceCollection Center of National Institute of Oceanographyand Fisheries, Alexandria under Code Numbers.
